                <note rend="inline" type="source">Doc. No. 12 bis (G).</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposal To Amend the Provisions of the Draft Treaty
                        Concerning Disputes on Boundary Demarcation</hi> (Art. 5)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1946-10-15T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1946-08-20T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Article</hi> 5</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Any questions which the Commissions are unable to agree will be referred to
                        an impartial third Commissioner appointed by agreement between the
                        interested parties. Should the parties fail to agree on this appointment the
                        third Commissioner will be appointed by the four Ambassadors acting as
                        provided for in Article 75.”</p>
                </quote>
            </div>
